FBIS3-31132 "dreeu031_h_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 HUNGARY Memorandum Rules Out Role in NATO Action LD1402204594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 2000 GMT 14 Feb 94 LD1402204594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] On no account will Hungary participate in a possible NATO military action on the territory of the former Yugoslavia. This is contained in the memorandum that was handed over today in Belgrade by a Hungarian Embassy official. Andras Vince also said that U.S. AWACS reconnaissance planes could not stay in Hungarian airspace in the case of a possible air strike. The embassy official said that Hungary's Embassy in Belgrade was not going to be evacuated for the time being. Belgrade radio and television have also reported the Hungarian Government's position.
